Preheat the #oven{} to 200 degrees. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Grate the @carrot{1}(grated on the coarse side of your grater) on the coarse side of your #grater{}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all!).

Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} and a knob of @butter{a knob}(if you have some) in a large #saucepan{} over medium high heat. Once hot, add the onion, tomatoes and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook until the onions are soft and the tomatoes have burst, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Once soft, stir in the garlic and @pasanda style seasoning{1}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the @basmati rice{150} and @raisins{40} to the pan. Stir to coat the rice in all the flavour.

Pour the @water for the rice{300} into the saucepan. Add the @chicken stock powder{1} and stir to dissolve. Bring to the boil. Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in it's own steam).

While the rice cooks, pop a large #frying pan{} over medium high heat. Season the @duck breasts{2} on both sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once hot, lay the duck in the pan skin-side down. > IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat! Cook until the skin is golden and crisp, ~{4-5%minutes}. Lower the heat to medium if it's browning too quickly. Turn and brown the flesh side for ~{1%minute} then transfer to a #baking tray{} skin side up.

Pop the baking tray onto the top shelf of the oven and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}. > IMPORTANT: The duck is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Once cooked, transfer your duck to a #cutting board{} or large #plate{} and cover with #foil{}. Leave to rest for a few mins.

Once everything is ready. Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and mix in the grated carrot and half the coriander. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} and share between your #bowls{}. Thinly slice the duck and lay on top of the rice. Drizzle over the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75} and sprinkle over the remaining coriander. Serve and Enjoy!